---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import HeaderTable from '../components/HeaderTable.astro';
---

<Layout title="Style Guide | DROO.FOO">
  <main>
    <HeaderTable 
      title="STYLE GUIDE" 
      version="v0.0.1" 
      updated="2024-12-22" 
      author="Drew Amor" 
      license="MIT" 
    />
    
    <h2 id="toc-title">Contents</h2>
    <ul class="incremental">
      <li><a href="#typography">Typography</a></li>
      <li><a href="#colors">Colors & Themes</a></li>
      <li><a href="#layout">Layout & Grid</a></li>
      <li><a href="#components">Components</a></li>
      <li><a href="#forms">Form Elements</a></li>
      <li><a href="#code">Code Display</a></li>
      <li><a href="#tables">Tables</a></li>
      <li><a href="#media">Media</a></li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="typography">Typography</h2>
    <p>
      This style guide uses <code>Monaspace Argon</code> for all text. It is a monospace font 
      that provides a clean, consistent grid layout while maintaining excellent readability.
    </p>

    <h3>Headings</h3>
    <div>
      <h1>Heading Level 1</h1>
      <h2>Heading Level 2</h2>
      <h3>Heading Level 3</h3>
      <h4>Heading Level 4</h4>
      <h5>Heading Level 5</h5>
      <h6>Heading Level 6</h6>
    </div>

    <h3>Text Styles</h3>
    <p>Regular paragraph text</p>
    <p><strong>Bold text</strong> using the strong element</p>
    <p><em>Italic text</em> using the em element</p>
    <p><code>Inline code</code> using the code element</p>
    <p><a href="#typography">Link text</a> using the anchor element</p>
    <p><mark>Highlighted text</mark> using the mark element</p>
    <p><del>Deleted text</del> using the del element</p>
    <p><ins>Inserted text</ins> using the ins element</p>
    <p><sub>Subscript</sub> and <sup>superscript</sup> text</p>
    <p><small>Small text</small> using the small element</p>
    <p><abbr title="Abbreviation">Abbr</abbr> using the abbr element</p>

    <h3>Lists</h3>
    
    <p>Unordered list:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>List item one</li>
      <li>List item two</li>
      <li>List item three with longer text that might wrap to multiple lines to demonstrate how line wrapping works with the monospace grid</li>
      <li>List item four</li>
    </ul>
    
    <p>Ordered list:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>First item</li>
      <li>Second item</li>
      <li>Third item with longer text that might wrap to multiple lines to demonstrate how line wrapping works with the monospace grid</li>
      <li>Fourth item</li>
    </ol>
    
    <p>Definition list:</p>
    <dl>
      <dt>Term 1</dt>
      <dd>Definition 1</dd>
      <dt>Term 2</dt>
      <dd>Definition 2 with longer text that might wrap to show how definition lists handle multi-line content in the monospace grid</dd>
    </dl>
    
    <p>Tree view list:</p>
    <ul class="tree">
      <li>Root
        <ul>
          <li>Branch 1
            <ul>
              <li>Leaf 1.1</li>
              <li>Leaf 1.2</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Branch 2
            <ul>
              <li>Leaf 2.1</li>
              <li>Leaf 2.2</li>
              <li>Leaf 2.3</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="colors">Colors & Themes</h2>
    <p>
      The design system supports three themes: light, dim, and dark. Each theme has its own color palette,
      with consistent application across all elements.
    </p>
    
    <h3>Primary Colors</h3>
    <div class="grid">
      <div style="background-color: var(--text-color); color: var(--background-color); padding: 1ch;">Text Color</div>
      <div style="background-color: var(--text-color-alt); color: var(--background-color); padding: 1ch;">Alt Text</div>
      <div style="background-color: var(--background-color); border: var(--border-thickness) solid var(--text-color); padding: 1ch;">Background</div>
      <div style="background-color: var(--background-color-alt); border: var(--border-thickness) solid var(--text-color); padding: 1ch;">Alt Background</div>
    </div>
    
    <h3>Accent Colors</h3>
    <div class="grid">
      <div style="background-color: var(--synthwave-purple); color: white; padding: 1ch;">Synthwave Purple</div>
      <div style="background-color: var(--synthwave-blue); color: black; padding: 1ch;">Synthwave Blue</div>
      <div style="background-color: var(--synthwave-green); color: black; padding: 1ch;">Synthwave Green</div>
      <div style="background-color: var(--synthwave-red); color: black; padding: 1ch;">Synthwave Red</div>
      <div style="background-color: var(--synthwave-pink); color: black; padding: 1ch;">Synthwave Pink</div>
    </div>
    
    <p>
      Use the theme toggle in the bottom right to switch between themes.
    </p>

    <h2 id="layout">Layout & Grid</h2>
    <p>
      The layout is based on a monospace grid, where each character occupies exactly the same amount of horizontal space.
      This creates a consistent, predictable layout system.
    </p>
    
    <h3>Grid System</h3>
    <p>The grid class creates flexible layouts with equal-width columns:</p>
    
    <h4>Two Column Grid</h4>
    <div class="grid">
      <div style="border: var(--border-thickness) solid var(--text-color); padding: 1ch;">Column 1</div>
      <div style="border: var(--border-thickness) solid var(--text-color); padding: 1ch;">Column 2</div>
    </div>
    
    <h4>Three Column Grid</h4>
    <div class="grid">
      <div style="border: var(--border-thickness) solid var(--text-color); padding: 1ch;">Column 1</div>
      <div style="border: var(--border-thickness) solid var(--text-color); padding: 1ch;">Column 2</div>
      <div style="border: var(--border-thickness) solid var(--text-color); padding: 1ch;">Column 3</div>
    </div>
    
    <h4>Four Column Grid</h4>
    <div class="grid">
      <div style="border: var(--border-thickness) solid var(--text-color); padding: 1ch;">Col 1</div>
      <div style="border: var(--border-thickness) solid var(--text-color); padding: 1ch;">Col 2</div>
      <div style="border: var(--border-thickness) solid var(--text-color); padding: 1ch;">Col 3</div>
      <div style="border: var(--border-thickness) solid var(--text-color); padding: 1ch;">Col 4</div>
    </div>

    <h2 id="components">Components</h2>
    
    <h3>Header Table</h3>
    <p>
      The HeaderTable component is used for document metadata:
    </p>
    <HeaderTable 
      title="COMPONENT EXAMPLE" 
      version="v1.0.0" 
      updated="2024-01-01" 
      author="Example Author" 
      license="MIT" 
    />
    
    <h3>Navigation</h3>
    <p>
      The main navigation appears at the top of every page.
    </p>
    
    <h3>Theme Toggle</h3>
    <p>
      The theme toggle appears at the bottom right of every page and allows switching between themes.
    </p>
    
    <h3>Horizontal Rule</h3>
    <hr>
    
    <h3>Blockquote</h3>
    <blockquote>
      <p>
        This is a blockquote. It can contain multiple paragraphs and other elements.
      </p>
      <p>
        Second paragraph in the blockquote.
      </p>
    </blockquote>
    
    <h3>Details/Summary</h3>
    <details>
      <summary>Click to expand details</summary>
      <p>
        This content is hidden by default and revealed when the summary is clicked.
      </p>
      <p>
        It can contain multiple paragraphs and other elements.
      </p>
    </details>

    <h2 id="forms">Form Elements</h2>
    
    <h3>Buttons</h3>
    <div class="grid">
      <button>Standard Button</button>
      <button style="background-color: var(--synthwave-purple); color: white;">Colored Button</button>
      <button disabled>Disabled Button</button>
    </div>
    
    <h3>Text Inputs</h3>
    <label>
      Text Input
      <input type="text" placeholder="Enter text here">
    </label>
    
    <h3>Checkbox and Radio</h3>
    <div>
      <label>
        <input type="checkbox"> Checkbox Option
      </label>
    </div>
    <div>
      <label>
        <input type="radio" name="radio-example"> Radio Option 1
      </label>
    </div>
    <div>
      <label>
        <input type="radio" name="radio-example"> Radio Option 2
      </label>
    </div>
    
    <h3>Select</h3>
    <label>
      Select Dropdown
      <select>
        <option>Option 1</option>
        <option>Option 2</option>
        <option>Option 3</option>
      </select>
    </label>
    
    <h3>Textarea</h3>
    <label>
      Textarea
      <textarea placeholder="Enter multiple lines of text here"></textarea>
    </label>

    <h2 id="code">Code Display</h2>
    
    <h3>Inline Code</h3>
    <p>
      Use the <code>&lt;code&gt;</code> element for inline code snippets.
    </p>
    
    <h3>Code Blocks</h3>
    <pre><code set:html={`// This is a code block
function example() {
  console.log("Hello, monospace world!");
  return true;
}`} /></pre>

    <h2 id="tables">Tables</h2>
    
    <h3>Basic Table</h3>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Header 1</th>
          <th>Header 2</th>
          <th>Header 3</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Row 1, Cell 1</td>
          <td>Row 1, Cell 2</td>
          <td>Row 1, Cell 3</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Row 2, Cell 1</td>
          <td>Row 2, Cell 2</td>
          <td>Row 2, Cell 3</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Row 3, Cell 1</td>
          <td>Row 3, Cell 2</td>
          <td>Row 3, Cell 3</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2 id="media">Media</h2>
    
    <h3>Images</h3>
    <figure>
      <img src="/images/foxheist1.png" alt="Fox Heist" style="max-width: 100%;">
      <figcaption>Fox Heist - Sample image</figcaption>
    </figure>
    
    <h3>Video</h3>
    <figure>
      <video 
        src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e0/The_Center_of_the_Web_%281914%29.webm" 
        controls=""
        style="max-width: 100%;">
        <a href="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e0/The_Center_of_the_Web_%281914%29.webm">
          The Center of the Web (1914), Wikimedia
        </a>
      </video>
      <figcaption>
        <a href="https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Page:The_Center_of_the_Web_(1914).webm/11">
          The Center of the Web (1914), Wikimedia
        </a>
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <h2>Final Notes</h2>
    <p>
      This style guide demonstrates the components and styling available in the monospace design system.
      It uses the Monaspace Argon font exclusively, and all elements are designed to align with the monospace grid.
    </p>
    <p>
      For more details on implementation, refer to the source code and CSS files.
    </p>
  </main>
</Layout> 
</Layout> 